    # [Answer it]"
    stop sound
    show sc day1office o06
    mc"Hmm..."
    show sc day1office o02
    mc"Hello?"
    ge"[y_name], is that you?"
    show sc day1office o05
    mc"Dad?"
    ge"Yeah it‚Äôs me. How have you been son?"
    show sc day1office o04
    mc"I‚Äôve been okay. Keeping busy as usual. Yourself?"
    show sc day1office o02
    ge"Pretty much the same. Our ship just ported in a town called Seaside, so I‚Äôve had some free time on my hands."
    ge"I called you at the house and just spoke to Nicole. She tells me that you have a new job down in Sunshine Bay."
    show sc day1office o04
    mc"Yeah‚Ä¶ You heard right. "
    show sc day1office o02
    jump lb_day1_gerald_call_1

label lb_day1_gerald_call_1:
    ge"And is it true that you are working with Ashley‚Äôs daughter [s_name]?"

label lb_day1_gerald_call_2:
    show sc day1office o04
    mc"I am Dad. She runs a hotel down here by the lighthouse, you remember the one?"
    show sc day1office o02
    ge"Yeah of course I do."
    ge"(Sigh‚Ä¶)"
    ge"What are you doing [y_name]?"
    show sc day1office o05
    mc"What do you mean by that Dad?"
    show sc day1office o02
    ge"You‚Äôre throwing your life away by being down there. What on earth were you thinking?"
    show sc day1office o03
    mc"Woah, hold up Dad. Where is this coming from?"
    show sc day1office o05
    ge"Are you doing this just to spite me? Is it because I wasn‚Äôt there for you enough? Is that it?"
    mc"No Dad, it has nothing to do with-"
    # (MC gets cut off)"
    ge"I knew it was a bad idea letting you study law."
    ge"I mean, it worked out well for Nicole sure, but you really should have followed in my footsteps like I wanted you to after you graduated from high school."
    ge"Or at least looked into applying for a government legal position, you certainly would have been smart enough."
    show sc day1office o03
    mc"Dad, we‚Äôve been over this a hundred times."
    mc"I didn‚Äôt get the promotion I wanted last week..."
    mc"So I‚Äôm helping [s_name] with her business while I wait to get another shot at being a senior associate with Nicole‚Äôs firm."
    show sc day1office o05
    mc"What‚Äôs so wrong about that?"
    ge"Everything! [s_name] is not your responsibility [y_name]."
    ge"Setting up your future with Nicole is. Well, it was supposed to be."
    ge"You didn‚Äôt have to travel all that way just to have a paying job, you could‚Äôve just called me, and I would‚Äôve found something for you temporarily."
    ge"What happened, did [s_name] and her mother guilt trip you into helping her?"
    show sc day1office o03
    mc"Dad, Ashley abandoned [s_name]. Her business is going to go under if I don‚Äôt help her turn things around."
    show sc day1office o05
    ge"Hmm, that‚Äôs typical Ashley, always giving up on others so easily."
    show sc day1office o03
    mc"No, not now Dad. We are not having that conversation."
    show sc day1office o05
    ge"You‚Äôre going to lose Nicole if you stay there, you hear me?"
    ge"Let‚Äôs be honest, that girl is the best thing that has ever happened to you."
    ge"She‚Äôs smart, attractive, and very goal oriented."
    ge"What could be more important than your relationship with her, that you chose to travel all that way to Sunshine Bay to be away from her for three whole months??"
    show sc day1office o03
    mc"Hey, she gave me her blessing I‚Äôll have you know."
    mc"And just because things didn‚Äôt work out between you and Ashley, doesn‚Äôt give you the right to hang this shit on me now Dad!"
    show sc day1office o05
    ge"Watch your tone with me son! You forget that I‚Äôm still your father."
    mc"Oh yeah‚Ä¶"
    show sc day1office o03
    jump lb_day1_gerald_call_3

label lb_day1_gerald_call_3:
    mc"Have you forgotten that [s_name] was only young when her mother took her away from us?"
    show sc day1office o05
    mc"She was like a daughter to you, and a sister to me, and you know it!"
    ge"I um‚Ä¶"
    show sc day1office o03
    mc"You know what Dad, things aren‚Äôt always what they seem, and life doesn‚Äôt always go the way you may have planned."
    mc"You of all people should know that. I mean it hasn‚Äôt gone to plan for either of us, especially after losing Mom‚Ä¶"
    mc"And then we had that time when the four of us were all living together‚Ä¶"
    mc"To me, it felt like having a real family again, even if it was only for a few years."

label lb_day1_gerald_call_4:
    mc"Look, I‚Äôm sorry if I never lived up to your expectations Dad, and I know you don‚Äôt want to hear this, but, I think I‚Äôm going to stay right here in Sunshine Bay with [s_name]."
    show sc day1office o05
    mc"I came here to do a job, and dammit, I‚Äôm going to see it through, whether you approve or not‚Ä¶"
    ge"You‚Äôll regret this decision my son. Mark my words, you‚Äôll regret this‚Ä¶"
    # (F hangs up, ends the call)"
    show sc day1office o03
    mc"Hello? Hello?"
    show sc day1office o20
    mc"(Fuck‚Ä¶ He‚Äôll never let go of the past. I wonder what else Nicole has told him.)"
    mc"(And what if he tells her the real truth about why I‚Äôm staying here and the problems with [s_name]‚Äôs business?)"
    mc"(I better pray that he doesn‚Äôt‚Ä¶)"
    show sc day1office o19
    mc"(Anyways, I can‚Äôt let that call with my Dad stop me from fixing things here‚Ä¶)"
    mc"(But what if Dad is right? What if I am throwing my life away, or putting my relationship with Nicole in jeopardy by being here?)"
    mc"(Shit‚Ä¶ This is too much for one person to deal with right now.)"
    mc"(I better go through these files and accounts.)"
    mc"(It should help to take my mind off the call with Dad and making any big decisions for the time being‚Ä¶)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc day1office o14
    with dissolve
    s"Hey [y_name], what are you up to?"
    show sc day1office o14
    mc"Well I‚Äôve gone right through all your figures for the past twelve months, and I think I‚Äôve managed to find a way to cut at least five thousand dollars out of your monthly costs."
    show sc day1office o10
    mc"As I said before, if you use the west wing of the hotel for guests..."
    mc"Then we can simply shut the electricity off at the breakers in the supply cabinet for the east wing, and any other areas on the grounds that aren't being used."
    mc"Mister Roshi would probably know which individual breakers to shut off in the fuse box for each section."
    mc"If business picks up, then we can switch the power back on and start using these areas again."
    show sc day1office o12
    s"That‚Äôs a great idea. Can I just say, that I think you‚Äôre amazing [y_name]?"
    show sc day1office o13
    s"And I really appreciate you taking the time to go through all of this for me, and for meeting my friends and Mister Roshi before."
    show sc day1office o10
    mc"No need to thank me. Besides, you‚Äôve done some great things yourself."
    mc"But there‚Äôs still plenty of work to do."
    show sc day1office o15
    s"Yes, of course."
    show sc day1office o07
    menu:
        "Mention the ‚Äúall women‚Äù issue"(wt="Best choice"):
            show sc day1office o08
            mc"Now, I think another major issue is the clientele that you‚Äôre trying to promote the hotel towards."
            show sc day1office o10
            s"Huh? How do you mean?"
            mc"I know you said that the hotel has certain traditions, the main one being that it only accommodates female guests."
            mc"But I believe that only allowing women to stay here is a big reason why the business is doing so poorly."
            mc"You‚Äôre missing out on making some serious coin by continuing to stick with a tradition that I‚Äôm sorry to say, is severely outdated."
            mc"Other hotels in the area or in Sunshine Bay are probably cashing in where you are missing out."
            mc"And that‚Äôs made even worse by the fact that you have the prime spot in town for travellers and tourists."
            show sc day1office o15
            s"I know [y_name], but even when I was running the hotel with my mother, all the guests were women."
            s"And anyone who has ever lived in Sunshine Bay knows what this place stands for."
            show sc day1office o11
            s"Changing those beliefs and those ideals now would be a huge decision to make."
            show sc day1office o08
            mc"Yeah, I took that into consideration."
            show sc day1office o07
            mc"Look, I actually admire the fact that you want to stick to the hotels traditions, I really do."
            show sc day1office o10
            mc"But I want you to at least have a think about it."
            mc"Promoting this place and accommodating for only women is all well and good, but what if you get six months down the track and you end up having to shut this place down?"
            show sc day1office o15
            s"If that happens, I may have wished that I‚Äôd listened to you, right?"
            mc"Yeah, quite possibly."
            mc"And if someone else buys up the area or even the hotel, they may not care for a hundred-year-old law, and then make the place open to everyone anyway."
            show sc day1office o11
            mc"You may have to bite the bullet, but that‚Äôs a decision for you to make, being the owner."
            s"(Sigh)‚Ä¶ I see your point."
            s"Look, I‚Äôll let you know if I change my mind. It‚Äôs not a decision I‚Äôm comfortable making right now."
            mc"Of course, no pressure. All I ask if that you give it some serious thought."
            $ s_points = change_stat(s_points,1,s_name)
            show sc day1office o13
            s"I will, I promise."
        "Don‚Äôt bring it up":
            #‚Äù (*Choosing this option will not allow any other men to stay at the hotel, closing any potential MMF scenes later in the game, but making MFF+ scenes possible)"
            show sc day1office o08
            mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ I really should talk to [s_name] about the hotel being open to females only.)"
            mc"(But perhaps I should mention this at a better time.)"
            mc"(Besides, who knows how long I‚Äôm even going to be here for?)"
    # (scene continues)"

    show sc day1office o15
    s"(I still don‚Äôt know for sure if [y_name] wants to stay or leave. I hope I‚Äôve been able to convince him enough to stay for the summer to help me.)"
    s"(The way he spoke with Vicky, the twins and Mister Roshi seemed pretty positive.)"
    s"(But it‚Äôs really hard to read his body language. I just wish I knew what he was thinking, or feeling.)"
    s"(I wonder if he still thinks about that last time we saw each other before Mom and I left all those years ago‚Ä¶)"
    # (MC looks closely at some paperwork)"
    show sc day1office o18
    s"(I better leave him be, as he looks really focused on what he‚Äôs reading.)"
    s"(I‚Äôm sure he‚Äôll call for me when he‚Äôs ready to talk some more‚Ä¶)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)






label lb_day1_mc_answer:
