    mc"(Oh shit! Is that really‚Ä¶ Ashley??)"
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom

    show sc day1beachashley a11
    mc"(She looks completely different from what I remember.)"
    mc"(She‚Äôs aged incredibly well.)"
    # (Show a different angle, showing off her figure)"
    mc"(And she‚Äôs changed her hairstyle too!)"
    # (Show a different angle of her hairdo)"
    show sc day1beachashley a08
    ash"Hey sweetheart."
    # (Ashley turns to the MC)"
    show sc day1beachashley a07
    ash"And who is this handsome young man?"
    show sc day1beachashley a05
    ash"Is he your boyfriend?"
    show sc day1beachashley a04
    s"My what??"
    show sc day1beachashley a40
    s"No, this is [y_name]!"
    jump lb_day1_big_conflict_ashley_1

label lb_day1_big_conflict_ashley_1:
    s"The only friend of mine that you made me abandon, remember?"

label lb_day1_big_conflict_ashley_2:
    show sc day1beachashley a06
    mc"I um, hi‚Ä¶"
    # (Ashley hugs MC, making friend even more angry for hugging him and not her)"
    $ v_char_ashley_known = True
    $ renpy.notify("Ashley has been added to the Relationship Menu.")
    show sc day1beachashley a08
    ash"Oh my god! Wow, look at you! You‚Äôve grown up a hell of a lot since we last saw each other!"
    show sc day1beachashley a06
    ash"What are you doing here in Sunshine Bay?"
    mc"Oh, well, [s_name] called me last week and asked if I could help her out with the hotel."
    show sc day1beachashley a05
    ash"Oh I see. Well it really is good to see you [y_name]. You certainly grew up to be a good-looking young man."
    mc"Oh, thanks I guess. Uhh, you look great too."
    show sc day1beachashley a11
    ash"Aww, such a charmer. Just like your Dad was when we first met."
    # (Friend stands there with her arms folded)"
    show sc day1beachashley a39
    s"Unbelievable‚Ä¶"
    show sc day1beachashley a03
    mc"(Okay, the tension between [s_name] and Ashley couldn‚Äôt be anymore obvious right now.)"
    mc"(And it hasn‚Äôt completely dissipated between me and [s_name] yet.)"
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ It doesn‚Äôt seem like this will be a peaceful reunion by any stretch‚Ä¶)"
    show sc day1beachashley a14
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day1beachashley a14b","v_rewards_ashley_01")
    ash"By the way, this is [s_name]‚Äôs aunt..."
    hide screen scr_rewards
    if renpy.loadable("extras.animations") and persistent.v_anim_enabled:
        window hide
        scene wip_01_trisha_intro  at tt_top
        pause
        window show
    else:
        show sc day1beachashley a15
    ash"Trisha."
    show sc day1beachashley a15
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc day1beachashley a15","sc day1beachashley a15x","v_pt_image_index_20")
    tri"Nice to meet you [y_name]. It‚Äôs so great of you to help [s_name] out like that."
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom

    show sc day1beachashley a16
    tri"Have you met my daughter [c_name] yet?"
    mc"Yeah uhh, we just went to the beach with her as she came down here for a surf.."
    mc"She‚Äôs gone to the hotel to get changed before she heads off."
    show sc day1beachashley a08
    ash"Oh it would be so great to see her too!"
    # (Friend angrily speaks up)"
    show sc day1beachashley a04
    s"Oh come on!! Are you seriously going to stand there and not even properly acknowledge me mother??"
    show sc day1beachashley a10
    ash"I um‚Ä¶ I‚Äôve wanted to honey. But I just didn‚Äôt know the right thing to say to you, especially after how we left things."
    show sc day1beachashley a04
    s"Well how about for starters, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm sorry for leaving you to handle the entire hotel by yourself [s_name]??‚Äù"
    s"I mean you left me a god-damn note to say you were heading off on holiday!"
    show sc day1beachashley a10
    ash"Look [s_name], I had a very good reason for leaving, I-"
    # (Ashley is cut off)"
    show sc day1beachashley a04
    s"Save it!"
    # (F puts her hand up, like a talk to the hand gesture)"
    show sc day1beachashley a19
    s"I don‚Äôt wanna hear another excuse from you, or some story about how your heart wasn‚Äôt in it anymore like with all your other jobs or projects Mom."
    s"I just convinced [y_name] to help me and then out of nowhere, YOU show up!"
    s"One day you‚Äôre here, the next you‚Äôre off somewhere else again!"
    # (Friend makes a frustrated face)"
    show sc day1beachashley a04
    s"Ughh!! I just can‚Äôt be around you right now!"
    show sc day1beachashley a34
    s"I'm out of here!"
    # (F storms off)"
    mc"[s_name] wait!"
    # (Ashley goes after her)"
    show sc day1beachashley a10
    mc"(Damn‚Ä¶ Well that was awkward.)"
    mc"(There‚Äôs clearly more to this friction between [s_name] and her mother that I don‚Äôt know about.)"
    mc"(Did Ashley really leave [s_name] a huge mess at the hotel without even saying anything to her before leaving town??)"


label lb_day1_ashley_explains:
    show sc day1beachashley a10
    ash"Sorry about that [y_name], Trisha. I think she just needs some time to cool off."
    show sc day1beachashley a06
    mc"What's going on Ashley?"
    mc"First [s_name] asks for your help to run her business, you disappear for several weeks and then show up out of nowhere, and then she goes ballistic and storms off."
    ash"What did she tell you exactly?"
    mc"She mentioned that you left the business to her, and that you left at the worst possible time."
    mc"Is what [s_name] saying true Ashley? Did you really abandon her?"
    mc"(I need to get to the bottom of this right away, even if it means that Ashley and I end up having a falling out.)"
    show sc day1beachashley a10
    ash"It‚Äôs not how it looks [y_name]. I just needed to go out of town for a few weeks."
    jump lb_day1_ashley_explains_1

label lb_day1_ashley_explains_1:
    ash"[s_name] is just exaggerating the situation."

label lb_day1_ashley_explains_2:
    show sc day1beachashley a29
    tri"Sorry to interrupt guys, but I‚Äôve just been messaged to come back into the office."
    tri"I swear the staff can‚Äôt do anything without me!"
    show sc day1beachashley a14
    ash"It‚Äôs fine. I‚Äôll explain everything to [y_name] for us."
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Whatever she‚Äôs going to tell me, clearly has something to do with Trisha too.)"
    show sc day1beachashley a30
    tri"Thanks sis."
    show sc day1beachashley a15
    tri"Nice meeting you [y_name]. I‚Äôm sure our paths will cross again in the near future."
    mc"Yeah, probably."
    show sc day1beachashley a42
    tri"Take care and say hi to my daughter if you see her. Bye!"
    # (Aunt leaves)"
    # (Ashley turns to the MC)"
    show sc day1beachashley a05
    ash"Let‚Äôs go for a walk [y_name], and find some place that we can sit down and talk‚Ä¶"
    stop ambient fadeout 1.0
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc day1beachashley a27
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/01/00/Beach_Ocean_Waves_-_Sound_Effect_decreased.mp3" loop fadein 1.0
    mc"So what happened between you and [s_name], Ashley? I need to know the truth."
    show sc day1beachashley a23
    ash"Okay, well there‚Äôs quite a bit to explain‚Ä¶"
    ash"I just needed to get away from everything for a couple of months, and I honestly thought [s_name] would be able to handle it. So did she I think."
    show sc day1beachashley a26
    ash"She‚Äôs had part-ownership of the business for a few years now, so I figured all would be okay, given how much time she‚Äôs spent working in and around the hotel. Looks like I was wrong."
    ash"The truth is [y_name], I never wanted anything to do with that hotel, even though my parents left it to me and Trisha in their will."
    show sc day1beachashley a23
    ash"I didn‚Äôt owe them anything and I didn‚Äôt ever want it to feel like they owed me anything either."
    ash"But rather than sell it off to someone else, Trisha and I thought it would be a good idea to pass the rights of the hotel over to [s_name] and [c_name], once they each had turned eighteen."
    ash"I don‚Äôt know what Trisha said to convince [c_name] to take over her share."
    show sc day1beachashley a26
    ash"But with [s_name], all I wanted was for her to have a business of her own, something she could use as an asset to perhaps set up her future, or to build upon for her next business. I guess that was a mistake."
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"You said that you didn‚Äôt want anything to do with the hotel? Does that include not helping [s_name] to run it as well?"
    show sc day1beachashley a23
    ash"Just because I haven‚Äôt been here the past few months, doesn‚Äôt mean that I haven‚Äôt tried to help [s_name] out [y_name]."
    ash"I left her with enough money and contacts to be able to run the place in case of an emergency."
    ash"And she had Mister Roshi to fix any maintenance issues if they came up."
    show sc day1beachashley a26
    ash"But deep down I knew that the hotel needed a lot of work, a lot more than only a few people can handle. I just didn‚Äôt know how to tell [s_name]."
    ash"I‚Äôve wanted so many times to tell her to sell the business to someone else, but then that would be going against the reason why I gave her my share of the business in the first place."
    show sc day1beachashley a23
    ash"[y_name], I know it doesn‚Äôt look good, but I really did have the best intentions for my daughters future."
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"I don‚Äôt mean to be rude Ashley, but from what I‚Äôve seen, it will take a miracle to save it from going under."
    mc"Answer me this, what happens to you if the hotel doesn‚Äôt survive? What‚Äôs going to happen to [s_name]?"
    show sc day1beachashley a26
    ash"I honestly haven‚Äôt thought that far ahead yet."
    ash"However, if you‚Äôre still here after everything she‚Äôs told you, then you must believe that there is a way to save the hotel from going into receivership."
    ash"Am I right?"
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"Well yeah, anything‚Äôs possible. That‚Äôs what I always like to believe."
    show sc day1beachashley a21
    ash"So what kind of work have you been doing? Did you join the navy like your father?"
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"Haha, not quite. I actually studied pre-law in college, and then I was close to being made a senior associate with the firm that I was working at."
    mc"However, that didn‚Äôt eventuate, and I‚Äôll have to wait until after the summer to apply with another firm."
    show sc day1beachashley a21
    ash"And let me guess, [s_name] called you not long after you didn‚Äôt get the position that you wanted, offering you the chance to work with her at the hotel."
    ash"Does that sound about right?"
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"Yeah, pretty much."
    show sc day1beachashley a21
    ash"I‚Äôd call that pretty incredible timing [y_name]. You know, [s_name] always looked up to you when we all lived together."
    ash"It may not have seemed like it at the time, but having you around meant so much to her."
    show sc day1beachashley a26
    ash"I‚Äôm just really sorry that I had to take her away from you, and the circumstances that surrounded that decision. I mean if your father-"
    # (MC cuts her off)"
    show sc day1beachashley a27
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day1beachashley a27b","v_rewards_ashley_02")
    mc"Could we please not talk about my Dad? Whatever happened between you two is your own business, not mine."
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"(I have my own problems with Nicole at present. So, having to go through the past again is not exactly what I need to hear right now.)"
    ash"Oh, if that‚Äôs what you want?"
    mc"Yeah, I‚Äôd really appreciate it if we didn‚Äôt go there."
    show sc day1beachashley a26
    ash"As you wish‚Ä¶"
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"Thanks. So um, if you don‚Äôt own the hotel or you‚Äôre not working there, what is it that you do for a living?"
    show sc day1beachashley a21
    ash"Oh, well I‚Äôm actually about to continue my archaeological work up in the mountains."
    show sc day1beachashley a22
    ash"As you may or may not know, I started a job in this field when I returned here to Sunshine Bay with [s_name]."
    show sc day1beachashley a24
    ash"Hey! You should stop by some time for a visit? That is, if you have the time to."
    show sc day1beachashley a21
    #[Act unsure / Act interested / Act disinterested]"
    menu:
        "Act unsure":
            show sc day1beachashley a25
            mc"Uhh‚Ä¶ Maybe that‚Äôs not such a wise idea Ashley."
            show sc day1beachashley a41
            ash"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Perhaps he just needs a little more coercing.)"
        "Act interested"(wt="Best choice"):
            #‚Äù +1 ASHLEY POINT"
            $ ash_points = change_stat(ash_points,1,"Ashley")
            show sc day1beachashley a28
            mc"Oh, well I guess I could do that."
            show sc day1beachashley a41
            show screen scr_rewards("sc day1beachashley a41b","v_rewards_ashley_03")
            ash"(Hmm‚Ä¶ He sounds interested, so that‚Äôs a start.)"
            hide screen scr_rewards
        "Act disinterested":
            #‚Äù -1 ASHLEY POINT"
            $ ash_points = change_stat(ash_points,-1,"Ashley")
            show sc day1beachashley a25
            mc"I don‚Äôt think that will be possible, as I‚Äôll be spending a lot of time with [s_name] fixing the hotel."
            show sc day1beachashley a26
            ash"It‚Äôs okay, I understand."
            show sc day1beachashley a41
            ash"(He seems really intent on helping [s_name]. Can‚Äôt say I blame him.)"


    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"Look, I know you have your own issues with the past, we all have..."
    mc"But I really do think that [s_name] needs your help Ashley, now, more so than ever."
    show sc day1beachashley a26
    ash"I know, it‚Äôs just not that simple sweetheart. I... I simply can't go back to that place anymore..."
    ash"It brings back old memories that I‚Äôve tried so hard to forget. But I don't want to bore you with all the details about my relationship with my parents."
    ash"All you need to know is that I‚Äôve always wanted the best for [s_name]."
    show sc day1beachashley a21
    ash"Speaking of which, do you think you could talk to her for me?"
    mc"Me? What do you want me to say to her?"
    show sc day1beachashley a28
    ash"Well, you two are obviously close again now after so long apart."
    mc"I wouldn‚Äôt exactly say we‚Äôre close."
    jump lb_day1_ashley_explains_3

label lb_day1_ashley_explains_3:
    ash"Well maybe not, but she still cares a lot about you, even after all this time."

label lb_day1_ashley_explains_4:
    show sc day1beachashley a23
    ash"Please, it would mean a lot if you could do this one favour for me."
    # (Ash places her hand upon the MC‚Äôs)"
    show sc day1beachashley a31
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day1beachashley a31b","v_rewards_ashley_04")
    ash"Will you do this for me?"
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc day1beachashley a28
    mc"(Sigh‚Ä¶)"
    mc"Okay, I‚Äôll see what I can do."
    ash"Thank you [y_name]. You were always so reliable, even when you were a kid."
    ash"So, I take it you have a girlfriend back home?"
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"Um, yes I do. What made you presume that?"
    show sc day1beachashley a28
    ash"A few reasons, a few tells. Being in law must have its advantages, something that women find really attractive."
    ash"Women want to be with intelligent men, in high paying jobs."
    show sc day1beachashley a24
    ash"I bet you look great in a suit too, hey?"
    show sc day1beachashley a28
    mc"Uhh, I suppose so."
    ash"I reckon you would. So what‚Äôs the lucky girl‚Äôs name?"
    mc"Her name? Oh, her name‚Äôs Nicole. She also works for a pretty prestigious law firm."
    ash"Ahh, now I see it. Let me guess‚Ä¶"
    ash"You two studied law together, or around about the same time, sparks began to fly..."
    show sc day1beachashley a24
    ash"And you both found out that you had a lot more in common after spending more and more time together, and not just with your chosen career paths."
    show sc day1beachashley a28
    mc"Well you almost nailed it, haha."
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"I was hesitant to study law in the beginning, but with Nicole‚Äôs help and guidance, she helped me through college. We ended up helping each other through that course."
    show sc day1beachashley a28
    ash"That‚Äôs great to hear [y_name]."
    jump lb_day1_ashley_explains_5

label lb_day1_ashley_explains_5:
    ash"She sounds like a great woman, especially if she‚Äôs okay with you travelling all the way down here to help [s_name] out for a few months, huh?"

label lb_day1_ashley_explains_6:
    mc"Uhh, yes she is."
    show sc day1beachashley a23
    ash"Three months. That‚Äôs a long time to be separated from someone you really care about."
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"You mean like you being away from [s_name]?"
    show sc day1beachashley a23
    ash"Ohh‚Ä¶ Darn it. I really made a fool myself there, didn‚Äôt I?"
    show sc day1beachashley a26
    mc"Yeah, yeah you did, haha!"
    ash"[y_name], there‚Äôs so much more to my relationship with my daughter that you don‚Äôt know about, and so many more things that I could tell you, that can‚Äôt be explained in one short afternoon chat."
    show sc day1beachashley a28
    ash"But if you really are sticking around to help [s_name] with the hotel, then I promise to tell you everything you want to know."
    ash"How does that sound?"
    mc"Sure, that would be great Ashley."
    mc"(Maybe I could ask her at another time if she has any details about the hotel from when her parents used to own it?)"
    mc"(It could be useful. The hotel was obviously popular at some point in the past, so they must have had some kind of blueprint for their own success.)"
    show sc day1beachashley a25
    mc"So you would like me to talk to [s_name] for you?"
    show sc day1beachashley a24
    ash"Yes, I would really appreciate it if you did. And as I said before, if you ever want to talk with me about anything‚Ä¶"
    # (Close up on Ashley‚Äôs eyes and lips here)"
    show sc day1beachashley a28
    ash"And I mean ‚Äúanything‚Äù, please, do not hesitate to give me a call."
    # (Ashley hands the MC her business card)"
    mc"Oh, thanks for the offer Ashley. I‚Äôll definitely consider it."
    mc"(Even despite the problems going on between her and [s_name], Ashley seems pretty friendly, and very easy to talk to.)"
    stop ambient fadeout 1.0
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc day1beachashley a05
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/01/00/Beach_Ocean_Waves_-_Sound_Effect_decreased.mp3" loop fadein 1.0
    ash"Okay, well‚Ä¶ I best be going then."
    # (they both stand up) "
    show sc day1beachashley a11
    ash"Thanks for being so understanding [y_name]. Hopefully we can do this again sometime soon."
    show sc day1beachashley a05
    mc"Yes, I‚Äôd like that."
    # (Ashley hugs the MC tight)"
    show sc day1beachashley a33
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day1beachashley a33b","v_rewards_ashley_05")
    ash"Be sure to give [s_name] a big hug and a kiss for me."
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc day1beachashley a32
    mc"Uhh, sure, will do!"
    # (Ashley pulls back and kisses him on the cheek)"
    $ renpy.sound.play("sound effects/01/01/short_kiss_sound_effect.mp3", loop=False, fadeout=1.0, fadein=1.0)
    show sc day1beachashley a35
    ash"Mwah!"
    stop sound
    show sc day1beachashley a36
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day1beachashley a36b","v_rewards_ashley_06")
    ash"Thanks for taking the time to hear me out [y_name]."
    # (Ashley holds his face in her hands)"
    show sc day1beachashley a37
    ash"Oh! You‚Äôre still so cute! Haha, later [y_name]‚Ä¶"
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc day1beachashley a35
    $ renpy.sound.play("sound effects/01/01/short_kiss_sound_effect.mp3", loop=False, fadeout=1.0, fadein=1.0)
    ash"Mwah!"
    stop sound
    mc"Uhh‚Ä¶ Bye Ashley."
    show sc day1beachashley a38
    mc"(She thinks I‚Äôm cute, still? Hmm‚Ä¶ Maybe she means it in a mother-son kind of way?)"
    mc"(Anyways, I better go and talk to [s_name], to see if I can make anymore sense of this friction between her and Ashley‚Ä¶)"
    stop ambient fadeout 1.0
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)





label lb_day1_s_comfort:
    scene sc day1eveintro i01
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/01/00/Night_Time_Sound_FX.mp3" loop fadein 1.0
    mc"(Okay, [s_name]‚Äôs probably in her room. Hopefully she‚Äôll let me talk to her, and that she‚Äôs calmed down by now.)"
    # (Cousin comes out of the front of the hotel)"
    show sc day1eveintro i02
    c"Hey, have you seen [s_name]? I thought I heard her enter the hotel, but I couldn‚Äôt find her."
    c"I just wanted to say goodbye to her before I left."
    mc"(It‚Äôs probably best that I don‚Äôt say anything to [c_name] about the argument that just happened before.)"
    mc"(She doesn‚Äôt need to know about any of that.)"
    show sc day1eveintro i04
    mc"Oh, um‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm not sure where she is to be honest. I can let her know you said goodbye when I see her if you want?"
    show sc day1eveintro i05
    c"Oh, thanks, that would be swell."
    show sc day1eveintro i04
    mc"I actually just met your Mom before, Trisha."
    c"Oh really, she was here?"
    mc"No, she was by the beach. And um, [s_name]‚Äôs Mom Ashley was there too."
    show sc day1eveintro i02
    c"Ohh‚Ä¶ So how did that go?"
    mc"I take it you know about the issues between her and [s_name]?"
    c"Not a hell of a lot, no."
    show sc day1eveintro i04
    c"But I do know that [s_name] said that she was going to tell Ashley what she thought of her when she returned to Sunshine Bay."
    c"Did she?"
    mc"Hmm‚Ä¶ It‚Äôs hard to say."
    c"Well, I hope she‚Äôs all right. Look, I really gotta get going."
    show sc day1eveintro i03
    c"I‚Äôve left my surfboard in storage if [s_name] asks. It was sure nice to meet you [y_name]."
    mc"You too [c_name]."
    c"I might call you tomorrow to further discuss this proposal of yours to teach me how to interact with other people."
    show sc day1eveintro i05
    c"So keep your phone on!"
    show sc day1eveintro i03
    mc"Haha, sure thing."

    #[Shake her hand / Say goodbye / Kiss her]"
    menu:
        "Shake her hand"(wt="Best choice"):
            #(MC offers to shake cousins hand)"
            show sc day1eveintro i30
            show screen scr_rewards("sc day1eveintro i30b","v_rewards_c_05")
            mc"It was nice meeting you [c_name]. "
            c"Yeah, it was nice to meet you too."
            $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,1,c_name)
            hide screen scr_rewards
            #+1 COUSIN POINT"
        "Say goodbye":
            show sc day1eveintro i05
            #(if this option is chosen, continues on to the next line by cousin below)"
        "Kiss her":
            #(MC leans in to kiss cousin on the cheek)"
            show sc day1eveintro i31
            show screen scr_rewards("sc day1eveintro i31b","v_rewards_c_06")
            c"Uhh‚Ä¶ What are you doing?"
            hide screen scr_rewards
            show sc day1eveintro i02
            mc"Sorry I, I was just going to give you a kiss on the cheek."
            c"Yeah, I‚Äôd rather you didn‚Äôt do that [y_name]. Personal space, you know?"
            mc"Oh, my mistake."
            $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,-1,c_name)
            mc"(That was a little presumptuous of me.)" #-1 COUSIN POINT"
            #(scene continues)"



    show sc day1eveintro i03
    c"Bye [y_name]."
    mc"Goodbye [c_name]."
    # (Cousin leaves, full behind shot as she leaves)"
    show sc day1eveintro i01
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ [c_name] seems like she‚Äôs pretty switched on, and I have a feeling she‚Äôll call back tomorrow.)"
    mc"(At least that‚Äôs one bit of positive news. Now to see if I can have [s_name] respond in a similar way‚Ä¶)"
    stop ambient fadeout 1.0
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # (MC knocks on friend‚Äôs door)"
    scene sc day1eveintro i06
    with dissolve
    play sound "sound effects/01/01/Door_Knock_Sound_Effect_Free.mp3" fadein 1.0
    "(Knock, knock, knock)"
    stop sound fadeout 1.0
    show sc day1eveintro i07
    s"Go away Mom!"
    mc"It‚Äôs me [s_name], [y_name]."
    # (F gets ups from her bed, wipes a tear from her eye and looks at the door)"
    s"Oh, sorry [y_name]. Please, come on in‚Ä¶"
    # (MC opens the door, sees F sitting on the end of her bed)"
    show sc day1eveintro i08
    mc"Hey you‚Ä¶ I just came to check to see if you were okay?"
    show sc day1eveintro i09
    s"Yeah I‚Äôm fine‚Ä¶ Why can‚Äôt things in my life just be easy?"
    s"Well, a lot easier than what I‚Äôm currently having to deal with?"
    s"It just feels like every time that I‚Äôm close to being somewhat happy, something shitty always happens to kill off that hope."
    show sc day1eveintro i16
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day1eveintro i16b","v_rewards_s_04")
    mc"That‚Äôs just life for you [s_name]..."
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc day1eveintro i19
    mc"Take the law firm job that I wanted for example‚Ä¶"
    mc"I thought for sure that I had the position I‚Äôd worked incredibly hard for..."
    mc"And within a few minutes of my meeting with the boss, I find out that I not only didn‚Äôt get the promotion, but I was also out of a job!"
    show sc day1eveintro i10
    mc"Life sometimes finds a way to kick you in the ass, and hard, and you don‚Äôt even see it coming!"
    s"That‚Äôs so true."
    show sc day1eveintro i11
    s"But you have so much more going on for you right now compared to my situation."
    show sc day1eveintro i19
    mc"Well one of the first things you should stop doing is comparing yourself with other people, even if it seems like I have things a hell of a lot better than you do [s_name]."
    # (Friend shoots the MC an unappreciative look, not happy with his reply)"
    show sc day1eveintro i10
    s"You know [y_name], I asked you to come here for your help, and I am truly grateful that you‚Äôre here. "
    show sc day1eveintro i11
    jump lb_day1_s_comfort_1

label lb_day1_s_comfort_1:
    s"But could you please stop with the jerk-like attitude?"

label lb_day1_s_comfort_2:
    show sc day1eveintro i10
    s"It‚Äôs getting very tiring‚Ä¶"
    show sc day1eveintro i19
    mc"Well I‚Äôm still here with you, am I not? Does it look like that any part of me is going to give up on you?"
    mc"Look‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm sorry that I walked out on you this morning, I was just frustrated. It‚Äôs been that kind of month."
    show sc day1eveintro i17
    mc"But the reality is, it feels like we‚Äôre starting from the ground floor of this business of yours, and we have a long way to get things right. "
    show sc day1eveintro i12
    mc"I had a shitty week back home before even arriving here..."
    mc"And I‚Äôm sorry I‚Äôm not all sunbeams and unicorns right now, especially after what I‚Äôve learned today."
    show sc day1eveintro i10
    s"What else did you learn then? Did you talk to my Mom?"
    mc"Yeah I did."
    show sc day1eveintro i17
    mc"We discussed a few things in brief, like the agreement you both made about the hotel, what her initial plans were for you when you took part ownership of the business."
    show sc day1eveintro i18
    mc"I think her heart was in the right place, it just wasn‚Äôt very well-thought-out is all."
    show sc day1eveintro i11
    s"Why does it sound like you‚Äôre taking her side in this, or feeling sorry for her?"
    show sc day1eveintro i19
    mc"I‚Äôm not taking anyone‚Äôs side here [s_name]."
    show sc day1eveintro i14
    s"Well you should be on my side, regardless of what my mother has told you."
    mc"Look, I‚Äôm just telling you my thoughts."
    mc"Whether they are right or wrong, how am I supposed to know the difference after being here for less than a day?"
    show sc day1eveintro i15
    s"You were exactly like this when we were kids [y_name]! You never paid attention to me, you spoke to me like you were talking to a god-damn wall!"
    s"All you cared about was your stupid video games."
    show sc day1eveintro i19
    mc"That‚Äôs not true."
    show sc day1eveintro i15
    s"Oh yeah‚Ä¶ You also couldn‚Äôt help but belittle me once you found out the truth about the hotel."
    s"Your tough-guy attitude towards me, purposely ignoring my phone calls, and now you‚Äôre siding with my mother."
    show sc day1eveintro i14
    s"Do you even care about me at all [y_name]? Or do you just take pleasure in upsetting me so much? "
    # (F turns away from the MC, trying her hardest not to cry.)"
    show sc day1eveintro i19
    mc"(Ohh geez‚Ä¶ She‚Äôs genuinely upset with me‚Ä¶ Have I really been acting like that much of an asshole to her?)"
    mc"(Did I really ignore her when we were kids?)"
    mc"(What if she‚Äôs right, and I simply didn‚Äôt notice or even realise?)"
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Maybe I have been a little harsh on [s_name], and I‚Äôve been taking all of my frustrations out on her after not getting that Senior Associate position last week.)"
    mc"(And on top of that, there‚Äôs the argument I had with my Dad earlier on, which certainly didn‚Äôt put me in a positive mood either.)"
    # (MC stands up and moves behind F, putting a hand on her shoulder)"
    show sc day1eveintro i10
    mc"[s_name], look, I‚Äôm really sorry. I apologise if I‚Äôve been hard on you, or if I‚Äôve upset you."
    mc"And I‚Äôm also sorry if I belittled or ignored you when we were young."
    show sc day1eveintro i12
    mc"That wasn‚Äôt fair, and you didn‚Äôt deserve that. Can we start over?"
    # (F turns to face the MC, upset, wipes a tear, and then gives him a slight smile)"
    show sc day1eveintro i14
    s"Um, okay, that would be nice..."
    show sc day1eveintro i20
    s"Sorry, I don‚Äôt usually get this emotional."
    show sc day1eveintro i25
    s"Normally I can handle these kinds of situations a lot better."
    mc"It‚Äôs okay. Dealing with parents can be hard work, even though it really shouldn‚Äôt be."
    show sc day1eveintro i26
    mc"But sometimes in life, it‚Äôs about how you react to a setback that shows a person‚Äôs true character, and how mentally tough they are."
    show sc day1eveintro i27
    s"Yeah, I know what you‚Äôre saying."
    show sc day1eveintro i21
    mc"Look, I know you don‚Äôt really want to talk about your Mom, but let me just say this‚Ä¶"
    mc"I have a feeling that there‚Äôs been some kind of misunderstanding between you both."
    show sc day1eveintro i26
    mc"And at some point, you should have a proper sit down with Ashley, and just get everything out in the open."
    mc"I‚Äôll even come with you if you‚Äôd like me to? You know, for extra support."
    # (MC places a hand upon Fs)"
    show sc day1eveintro i27
    s"Oh, that would be great [y_name], thank you."
    show sc day1eveintro i24
    s"But I‚Äôm not quite ready to confront my Mom again."
    mc"That‚Äôs all right, no pressure. Besides, we have plenty of other important issues to take care of now, don‚Äôt we?"
    show sc day1eveintro i28
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day1eveintro i28b","v_rewards_s_05")
    s"Haha, yes we do."
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc day1eveintro i20
    mc"Look, it‚Äôs almost nighttime, so we won‚Äôt get much more work in for the day even if we wanted to."
    show sc day1eveintro i26
    mc"How about we get away from the hotel for a couple of hours?"
    show sc day1eveintro i25
    s"Really? You want to do something with me tonight?"
    mc"Yeah of course."
    show sc day1eveintro i26
    mc"Besides, I haven‚Äôt even seen what the town looks like at night, and perhaps you could show me to some of the best places to go in Sunshine Bay, now that it's after sunset?"
    show sc day1eveintro i28
    s"Oh yes, I‚Äôd love to!"
    show sc day1eveintro i23
    mc"Great! Well how about I go and close the office for the day, get changed into something more appropriate, and then I‚Äôll meet you out the front of the hotel in say, half an hour from now?"
    s"That sounds like a very good plan! Okay, I‚Äôll meet you there soon."
    show sc day1eveintro i27
    mc"Sure thing."
    #show screen toprightmenu
    s"And [y_name]? Thanks for cheering me up. I really needed it."
    mc"No problems at all [s_name]‚Ä¶"
    # (screen goes blank)"
    mc"See you in a bit."
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)




label lb_day1_getting_away:
    scene sc day1eve e01
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/01/00/Night_Time_Sound_FX.mp3" loop fadein 1.0
    mc"(I‚Äôm really looking forward to this.)"
    mc"(After such an eventful day, it would be great to take our minds off the hotel, family and any other such problems that may cause an argument.)"
    show sc day1eve e02
    mc"(I don‚Äôt like fighting with [s_name], but she‚Äôs certainly made it easy for me to be angry with her.)"
    mc"(She‚Äôs trying to make amends though, so I can‚Äôt knock her for that.)"
    show sc day1eve e03
    s"I‚Äôm ready to go [y_name]."
    # (MC turns, sees F who has changed)"
    # ROLLING WIP OF F IN DIFFERENT CLOTHES"
    show sc day1eve e04
