label lb_day1_evening_dinner:
    scene sc day1eve e26
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day1eve e26b","v_rewards_s_07")
    play ambient "sound effects/03/01/town_street_night_ambience.mp3" loop fadein 1.0
    s"How about this place? Is this where we should have some dinner?"
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc day1eve e28
    mc"Well maybe you should decide for us [s_name]? This is your town, remember?"
    show sc day1eve e29
    s"All right then smart guy."
    # (She gives him a wry smile, raised eyebrow)"
    show sc day1eve e28
    mc"Okay fine, this place I‚Äôm sure will do."
    show sc day1eve e27
    s"So how did you find the ride on my scooter?"
    menu:
        "It was horrible":
            show sc day1eve e65
            mc"It was a truly horrible experience [s_name]. I think I might walk back to the hotel after we have dinner."
            show sc day1eve e64
            s"Oh come on [y_name], it wasn‚Äôt that bad. I think you‚Äôre over-exaggerating things."
            show sc day1eve e30
            mc"Hmm, perhaps..."
            mc"But I could‚Äôve done without eating a shitload of your hair during the ride though."
            $ s_points = change_stat(s_points,-1,s_name)
            #-1 FRIEND POINT"
        "It was okay"(wt="Best choice"):
            show sc day1eve e30
            mc"Um, the ocean breeze was nice I‚Äôll admit. So it was okay I guess."
            show sc day1eve e65
            mc"Aside from me eating a shitload of your hair that is!" #+1 FRIEND POINT"
            $ s_points = change_stat(s_points,1,s_name)
        "Never again":
            show sc day1eve e64
            mc"Oh my god, never again! This thing is an accident waiting to happen!"
            s"Wait, are you serious? Scooters are the safest form of transport [y_name]."
            mc"If you say so."
            $ s_points = change_stat(s_points,-1,s_name)
            mc"Maybe if I was the one driving then I wouldn‚Äôt have had to eat a shitload of your hair during the ride."

    show sc day1eve e64
    s"Oh my god, really?? Sorry, I should‚Äôve tied it up in a ponytail, or even tucked it under my helmet before we took off."
    show sc day1eve e28
    mc"It‚Äôs cool, I‚Äôm fine. But I probably won‚Äôt need an appetiser now."
    mc"At least your hair smelled nice though."
    show sc day1eve e31
    s"Oh haha... You should count yourself lucky that I shampooed my hair before we went out."
    s"Come on, let‚Äôs go get some real food."
    mc"Sounds good‚Ä¶"
    stop ambient fadeout 1.0
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # (MC and F sit down in the quiet restaurant for dinner)"
    # (MD - I quite like this setting mate - https://www.daz3d.com/burger-restaurant)"
    scene sc day1eve e33
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/02/01/quiet_restaurant_ambient_noise.mp3" loop fadein 1.0
    s"So what‚Äôs your first impression of this burger place?"
    mc"It‚Äôs okay, but it‚Äôs pretty quiet in here though. Is that a bad sign?"
    show sc day1eve e34
    s"I wouldn‚Äôt say so. We‚Äôre here early, and it‚Äôs also a weeknight. What are the restaurants like where you live?"
    show sc day1eve e33
    mc"Oh, the ones close to us are all pretty trendy establishments. Nicole and I don‚Äôt really like to eat out much to be honest."
    mc"We prefer to cook at home, to save money and all that."
    show sc day1eve e38
    s"I guess when you have a mortgage you have to make sacrifices like that, right?"
    show sc day1eve e33
    mc"Exactly. All this time studying law and then paying off our place has made me mindful of where I‚Äôm spending my money."
    show sc day1eve e34
    s"It almost sounds like you should‚Äôve worked in a bank, or been an accountant instead?"
    mc"Haha, perhaps. Don‚Äôt get me wrong, I‚Äôm not a complete tight-ass when it comes to spending money."
    show sc day1eve e33
    mc"I mean I do like to splash out every now and then, that is if the occasion calls for it. So, what‚Äôs good to eat here?"
    # (MC looks at his menu)"
    show sc day1eve e39
    s"It depends on how hungry you are?"
    s"If you just want a lighter meal, then just a basic hamburger and fries will do the trick."
    show sc day1eve e40
    s"However, if you‚Äôre not worried about your figure for one night, then I recommend you get this one‚Ä¶"
    # (F points to a burger on her menu)"
    s"The Uni-burger‚Ä¶"
    s"It‚Äôs made with fresh and never frozen, one hundred percent, AAA Donutistan beef, tomatoes, lettuce, beetroot, sliced cheese and their famous Uni-burger sauce, served on a Melody potato roll."
    show sc day1eve e36
    s"With of course, extra bacon, and some of the best fries you‚Äôre ever likely to eat!"
    show sc day1eve e33
    mc"Cool. By the way, who‚Äôs Melody?"
    show sc day1eve e34
    s"Uhh, I think they‚Äôre referring to the singer-songwriter. I‚Äôm not overly sure."
    s"I think they slapped her name on their famous potato rolls as part of an advertising campaign she did for their restaurant chain recently."
    mc"I see. All right, well how about I give that one a go then?"
    show sc day1eve e36
    s"Great! Wait here, while I go and order for us‚Ä¶"
    # (A shot of F leaving the table to go and order)"
    show sc day1eve e34
    mc"Thanks [s_name]."
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc day1eve e34
    with dissolve
    s"So while we‚Äôre waiting for our orders, maybe we should talk."
    mc"Yeah, I think we should."
    show sc day1eve e32
    mc"But how about we don‚Äôt talk about the business or your Mom?"
    mc"Or anything that could be a touchy subject."
    show sc day1eve e39
    s"Yes! I agree. But what should we discuss?"
    # [Other careers / About [c_name] ]"
    show sc day1eve e33

    jump lb_day1eve_menu

label lb_day1eve_menu:
    if v_day1_eve_othercareers == True and  v_day1_eve_aboutc == True:
        jump lb_day1eve_menu_end
    menu:
        "Other careers":
            if v_day1_eve_othercareers == False:
                $ v_day1_eve_othercareers = True
                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"How about I ask you something hypothetical?"
                mc"Like for instance, if you weren‚Äôt running the hotel, what would you want to do for a career?"
                mc"I mean surely there‚Äôs something else that you would have hoped to do before you started running it?"
                show sc day1eve e34
                s"Oh, well, I had a few ideas in mind. At one point I really had my heart set on a job that involved travelling."
                mc"Like what exactly?"
                s"Well at first I thought that I could be a travel agent."
                show sc day1eve e36
                s"That way, I would become quite knowledgeable with destinations all over the world, and I‚Äôd also get cheaper flights."
                show sc day1eve e34
                s"Another job I would have liked to apply for is a retail buying assistant for a major airline."
                mc"Oh, that sounds very specific."
                s"Yeah, a good friend of mine Harmony who I went to college with does that kind of work."
                mc"And what does her job entail?"
                s"She mainly supports the airline by managing purchase orders, monitoring inventory, preparing budgets and providing administrative support."
                s"She works very close with the vendor and keeps track of market trends."
                mc"She sounds like a busy woman!"
                show sc day1eve e35
                s"That she is! But the discounts she gets on flights are ridiculous!"
                s"She‚Äôs already been overseas three times this year!"
                show sc day1eve e34
                mc"Which she‚Äôd probably write-off as a tax expense no doubt."
                show sc day1eve e33
                s"I guess so. I found out early on that I didn‚Äôt have the qualifications or experience to even be considered."
                mc"What about being a flight attendant? Was there ever a time you wanted to apply for that kind of role?"
                show sc day1eve e32
                s"There was, but it didn‚Äôt last very long."
                mc"How come?"
                show sc day1eve e38
                s"Well, I didn‚Äôt exactly fit the role, nor did I have the specific features that most airlines are looking for in an air hostess."
                show sc day1eve e33
                menu:
                    "You‚Äôre right":
                        mc"Yeah, you‚Äôre probably right."
                        mc"The big airlines are quite judgemental like that and you probably didn‚Äôt fit the profile."
                        mc"To be honest, I couldn‚Äôt see you in a role like that which is of huge importance."
                        show sc day1eve e32
                        s"Oh, well, I guess they didn‚Äôt either." #-1 FRIEND POINT"
                        #(Friend looks disappointed by the MC‚Äôs response)"
                        $ s_points = change_stat(s_points,-1,s_name)
                    "You‚Äôre perfect"(wt="Best choice"):
                        show sc day1eve e33
                        mc"What the hell do you mean?? You‚Äôd make a perfect airline hostess [s_name]!"
                        show sc day1eve e34
                        s"Apparently not. I mean, if you haven‚Äôt noticed, my butt is a little too big for that kind of job."
                        s"And I‚Äôm convinced that‚Äôs all anyone would see if they were to look down the aisle if I was walking through it."
                        mc"They really judge people with that specific feature?"
                        s"Uh-huh."
                        show sc day1eve e33
                        s"Well, they wouldn‚Äôt tell someone in person, but that‚Äôs what some girls who have an ass like mine, who didn‚Äôt succeed with job interviews, seem to believe."
                        jump lb_day1eve_menu_1

                        label lb_day1eve_menu_1:
                        mc"Hmm‚Ä¶ I still think you‚Äôd be a great air hostess [s_name]."
                        mc"You‚Äôre gorgeous and uhh, seeing your butt if I were on your flight wouldn‚Äôt bother me at all."

                        label lb_day1eve_menu_2:
                        show sc day1eve e35
                        s"Haha, you‚Äôre real sweet [y_name]."
                        show sc day1eve e34
                        mc"(I hope that didn‚Äôt sound weird the way I said it. I was just trying to be sincere.)"
                        $ s_points = change_stat(s_points,1,s_name)
                        #+1 FRIEND POINT"
                    "They‚Äôre crazy":
                        show sc day1eve e33
                        mc"What are you talking about [s_name]? They‚Äôre crazy if they think you wouldn‚Äôt make an awesome airline hostess."
                        show sc day1eve e38
                        s"Oh, you think so [y_name]?"
                        show sc day1eve e33
                        mc"Yeah I do. I mean if it‚Äôs one thing that airlines are lacking in nowadays it‚Äôs sex appeal. And you‚Äôve got that in abundance [s_name]!"
                        show sc day1eve e34
                        s"Uhh, thanks [y_name]."
                        show sc day1eve e38
                        s"(I don‚Äôt think he really knows much about air hostesses at all.)" #-1 FRIEND POINT"
                        $ s_points = change_stat(s_points,-1,s_name)

                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"So uhh, where do you think this interest in travelling came from?"
                show sc day1eve e34
                jump lb_day1eve_menu_3

                label lb_day1eve_menu_3:
                s"Oh I guess I got that from your Dad, knowing that he‚Äôd been to so many places around the world with the Navy..."
                s"And seeing him leave home so many times while we were living together obviously stuck in my mind."
                s"I suppose I wanted to do the same at one stage in my life."

                label lb_day1eve_menu_4:
                mc"Well, there‚Äôs no reason why you still couldn‚Äôt do so [s_name]."
                show sc day1eve e37
                s"Yeah, hopefully one day. I don‚Äôt think I could do it by myself though."
                show sc day1eve e34
                s"I always pictured having a travelling companion with me."
                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"You mean like Brodie?"
                show sc day1eve e32
                s"Uhh, perhaps."
                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"Have you ever mentioned any of this to him?"
                show sc day1eve e32
                s"No, I haven‚Äôt. Travelling together is not the kind of thing that we talk about when we see each other."
                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"Well maybe you should put it out there the next time you see him. It doesn‚Äôt hurt to ask though, right?"
                show sc day1eve e34
                s"Yeah, I guess so."
                jump lb_day1eve_menu

            mc"(We've already talked about this.)"
            jump lb_day1eve_menu

        "About [c_name]":
            if v_day1_eve_aboutc == False:
                $ v_day1_eve_aboutc = True
                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"So, how confident are you that [c_name] will want to work with us?"
                show sc day1eve e32
                s"When we first put the idea to her, I didn‚Äôt think she‚Äôd be interested, as I know how stand-offish she can be around other people."
                show sc day1eve e34
                s"But I noticed her facial expressions and her body language changed once you asked her about teaching surfing lessons to the hotel guests."
                show sc day1eve e33
                s"I have to ask, what prompted you to even suggest that to [c_name]?"
                mc"I don‚Äôt know really‚Ä¶"
                mc"There was a moment when we were watching her surf this afternoon, and all of a sudden an idea popped in my head."
                mc"Seeing as we have nothing to lose with the hotel, I figure that we should try some new things."
                mc"Hopefully [c_name] buys into the idea because I think she‚Äôd be great at it."
                show sc day1eve e39
                s"I have a great feeling that she will too. You know, she doesn‚Äôt normally talk with people as openly as she did with you this afternoon, so that‚Äôs a positive sign."
                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"The trick is to get her to do the same with other people. But don‚Äôt worry. I‚Äôll take care of that, presuming we get her on board."
                mc"I actually spoke to [c_name] before she left this afternoon, and she said she‚Äôll probably give us a call tomorrow some time."
                show sc day1eve e35
                s"That‚Äôs awesome [y_name]!"
                show sc day1eve e34
                s"I‚Äôve tried for ages to get [c_name] to give me some help at the hotel, but I could never seem to convince her."
                show sc day1eve e35
                s"You must have a magician-like way with words or something??"
                show sc day1eve e34
                menu:
                    "I‚Äôm amazing":
                        show sc day1eve e33
                        mc"What can I say. I am amazing!"
                        show sc day1eve e35
                        s"Haha, cocky much [y_name]?"
                        show sc day1eve e34
                        mc"You know it [s_name]!"
                        show sc day1eve e35
                        s"Hahaha!"
                    "I got lucky"(wt="Best choice"):
                        show sc day1eve e33
