                s"Can I ask you a question now?"
                mc"Yeah, of course you can."
                show sc day1eve e33
                jump lb_day1eve_menu_5

                label lb_day1eve_menu_5:
                s"Do you hear from your Dad often?"

                label lb_day1eve_menu_6:
                mc"Uhh, I spoke to him a few hours ago actually."
                s"Oh really? How is he? What did he want?"
                mc"He‚Äôs okay I guess. He uhh, he knows that I‚Äôm down here helping you."
                show sc day1eve e32
                s"Really? Did you tell him?"
                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"No um, he called at the house for me and spoke to Nicole, who told him everything."
                show sc day1eve e32
                s"And was he happy that you came down to Sunshine Bay to see me, and to help out?"
                show sc day1eve e33
                mc"Not exactly‚Ä¶ He thinks that I‚Äôm throwing my life and my career away by being here, and that..."
                mc"I‚Äôm only doing it to spite him."
                show sc day1eve e38
                s"Why on earth would he think that?"
                show sc day1eve e32
                mc"He believes it‚Äôs because he wasn‚Äôt there enough for me when I was a kid, especially after you and your Mom left."
                mc"But it has nothing to do with that. He just doesn‚Äôt understand."
                mc"I made this decision with Nicole, he just doesn‚Äôt want to believe that."
                show sc day1eve e38
                s"I‚Äôm really sorry if I put you in that position [y_name]."
                mc"Nah, it‚Äôs not your fault."
                show sc day1eve e32
                jump lb_day1eve_menu_7

                label lb_day1eve_menu_7:
                mc"I think my Dad is still bitter about Ashley leaving with you the way that she did."
                mc"He‚Äôs never really told me what their fights were about, but I do know that he still has some ill feeling towards her."
                show sc day1eve e38
                s"My Mom would never discuss your Dad with me."
                s"I think she liked to pretend that her relationship with him never even existed, which is what made me even more angry with her when she was so happy to see you."
                show sc day1eve e32
                s"Oh! Sorry, that wasn‚Äôt meant to sound the way that it did."

                label lb_day1eve_menu_8:
                mc"That‚Äôs all right, I know what you meant."
                show sc day1eve e33
                s"So you and your Dad had a fight then?"
                mc"Yeah we did. The chat ended with him hanging up on me. I swear he‚Äôs becoming more and more bitter the older he gets."
                s"Where did it all go wrong for them?"
                s"They seemed so happy together, so happy in love, and then those last few weeks before we moved out, they became two completely different people."
                mc"I honestly wish I knew. But hey, at least you were eventually able to get in contact with me."
                show sc day1eve e34
                mc"So it‚Äôs not all bad I guess."
                # (F smiles and they both have their hands on the table, close to each other)"

                jump lb_day1eve_menu

            mc"(We've already talked about this.)"
            jump lb_day1eve_menu


