    jump lb_day2_mc_c_date1_3

label lb_day2_mc_c_date1_3:
    mc"Yes and no. I mean, we‚Äôve never argued about my Dad and her Mom dating. Which is quite surprising actually."
    mc"Besides, I don‚Äôt see why you would think there are problems between us, I mean, I did still come all the way down here to help her, remember? "
    c"So you‚Äôre saying that you and [s_name] are doing fine?"
    mc"Well, we‚Äôre okay I guess. I suppose it‚Äôs because we‚Äôre like siblings or something."
    mc"We‚Äôve just had a couple of minor disagreements that are stressing us both out.."
    show sc day2cdate1 c39
    c"It sounds like you both need to find your centre [y_name], haha!"
    mc"Haha, you very well could be right."
    c"Talk to her. You two should be working together, not against each other."
    c"I‚Äôm sure your problems can be worked out."
    show sc day2cdate1 c38
    c"I mean, I would have loved to have had someone like [s_name] around when I was growing up."

label lb_day2_mc_c_date1_4:
    mc"(Hmm.. She‚Äôs right. Life‚Äôs too short to constantly be arguing with someone.)"
    mc"(I‚Äôve had enough of that with Nicole of late, I certainly don‚Äôt want that to keep continuing with [s_name].)"
