        mc"(I should get back out there and talk to the rest of the girls.)"
        scene black
        with dissolve
        scene black
        with Pause (2)
        scene sc day2call c01
        with dissolve
        $ v_calling = True
        show screen char_call_null
        mc"(All right, who should I call next?)"
        window hide
        $ renpy.choice_for_skipping()
        call screen char_call_active




label lb_day2_twins_date1:
    # (SOW) 07 - MC visits The Twins"
    # - The MC is talking to his Best Friend"
    # SCENE BEGINS"
    $ v_calling = False
    $ v_char_twins_cancall = False
    $ v_char_twins_date = 2
    scene sc day2twdate1 t01
    with dissolve
    mc"(This must be their main office that they work from.)"
    mc"(There they are. But which one is which?)"
    # (MC stands at the other side of the desk that Lily is sitting behind)"
    show sc day2twdate1 t22
    mc"Ahem!"
    show sc day2twdate1 t05
    lily"Oh, [y_name]! Good timing."
    show sc day2twdate1 t03
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc day2twdate1 t03","sc day2twdate1 t03x","v_pt_image_index_31")
    mc"Lily, I presume?"
    lily"Very good. It looks like your fifty-fifty guesses are starting to balance out for you."
    mc"Haha, I‚Äôm picking up a few differences between you two."
    # (MC sees Ivy is on a phone call)"
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom

    show sc day2twdate1 t07
    mc"Your sister looks like she‚Äôs on a pretty important call there."
    # (Make sure Lily has this intense, angry look on her face like she wants to strangle the guy on the other end of the phone)"

    lily"Yeah, she‚Äôs been on the phone for about an hour now, dealing with this client that is very particular about some last-minute suggestions he‚Äôd like to add in."
    lily"It's for this party he‚Äôs paid us to organise and host for his son‚Äôs twenty-first birthday this Saturday night."
    show sc day2twdate1 t07
    mc"She looks quite frustrated, as if she‚Äôs ready to kill whoever is on the other end of the line. "
    show sc day2twdate1 t03
    lily"Who, Ivy? Nah, that‚Äôs just her resting bitch face."
    lily"Inside she‚Äôs quite calm and relaxed, and knows that she just has to hold out until this guy has nothing else to tell her."
    show sc day2twdate1 t04
    lily"This party is worth a lot of money to us, and sometimes you have to take the rough with the smooth. This being an example of the ‚Äúrough‚Äù."
    mc"Hehe, sure looks like it."
    show sc day2twdate1 t03
    lily"Anyway, enough about that. Please, take a seat."
    mc"Thanks."
    # (The MC sits to the side of Lily‚Äôs desk, she faces him with her legs crossed, interested in what he has to say)"
    # e.g. https://image1.masterfile.com/getImage/NjEwMi0wNjAyNjA1NmVuLjAwMDAwMDAw=ALv2fb/6102-06026056en_Masterfile.jpg"
    # https://previews.123rf.com/images/lightfieldstudios/lightfieldstudios1805/lightfieldstudios180504495/102889066-young-businesswoman-in-black-dress-and-glasses-sitting-in-a-chair-at-office-with-legs-crossed.jpg"
    # https://media.istockphoto.com/photos/businesswoman-in-office-chair-with-straight-back-and-crossed-legs-picture-id534220461"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc day2twdate1 t11
    with dissolve
    lily"So, you wanted to discuss a few things you were saying?"
    mc"Yes I would."
    mc"First off, I just wanted you to know that I‚Äôve taken a look at your credentials online, and I gotta say it‚Äôs very impressive."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"Thank you [y_name]. My sister and I have worked very hard to build our business gradually, so we can eventually sell it off and retire early."
    mc"That‚Äôs very ambitious of you both."
    show sc day2twdate1 t13
    lily"Well, we‚Äôd like to be able to do other things aside from working."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"We both manage to have a pretty active social life and if we‚Äôre lucky, we sometimes get invited to party with the clients whose events we‚Äôre organising for them."
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    mc"Yeah I read that you and Ivy once partied with a bride and groom at their wedding reception, and you two were the last to leave!"
    show sc day2twdate1 t13
    lily"Haha yeah, that was a memorable night, as was the honeymoon, so we heard."
    show sc day2twdate1 t17
    lily"That‚Äôs what we‚Äôre all about [y_name]. We get to know all about the people who we‚Äôre working for."
    show sc day2twdate1 t15
    lily"That way, we know we‚Äôre not wasting our time and that the client isn‚Äôt a complete jerk-off who is going to stiff us on payment or screw us around."
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    mc"You two really go all-in by the sound of it?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t13
    lily"Oh yeah, we go balls-deep if we have to."
    mc"(Gulp!)"
    show sc day2twdate1 t15
    lily"Anyway, you were going to ask me something I believe?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    mc"Yes I was."
    mc"Now regarding the hosting of functions at the hotel, what kind of information do you think would be useful to you and your sister?"
    mc"I‚Äôve gone over the financial records and spendings for the past quarter and a lot of other paperwork."
    mc"In your expertise, what should I be looking for?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"What about the history of the hotel? Do you know much about it?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    mc"Aside from it only catering to females, and that [s_name]‚Äôs grandparents used to own it, not much else."
    show sc day2twdate1 t17
    lily"Well, seeing as we‚Äôre potentially going to be hosting some events there ourselves in the near future..."
    lily"I‚Äôd start by looking at what functions were popular at the hotel when it was at its peak."
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    lily"[s_name]‚Äôs grandparents, or even the owners before them, what kind of parties would they allow to be hosted on the grounds?"
    lily"Ivy and I were looking to check it out properly tomorrow and to take some photos as well."
    lily"It‚Äôs so we can pitch some ideas to clients who are currently on our books who we know like to visit and stay in Sunshine Bay each summer."
    lily"We need to get you and [s_name] some business quick-smart, and my sister and I feel that this is one of the fastest ways to do that."
    mc"So you pitch some event ideas or suggestions to us, and  your clients, and then we go from there?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t15
    lily"More or less, yes. We still have to figure out exact numbers, the maximum capacity your venue can hold."
    show sc day2twdate1 t17
    lily"But the idea is to sell the hiring of the room to host the party, as a package deal."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"It would be coupled with clients, businessmen and women, staying at the hotel for a night, maybe even them checking in Friday afternoon and leaving Monday morning."
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    mc"Well, if I thought I was impressed before, you two have prepared incredibly well for this."
    show sc day2twdate1 t14
    lily"That‚Äôs how we roll, haha!"
    show sc day2twdate1 t17
    lily"And it helps that Ivy and I studied hotel management as one of our courses at college."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"Mind you, I never completed it."
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Just like [s_name]. I guess it‚Äôs a lot more common for young people to not see a college course through until the end.)"
    lily"My sister and I changed classes to take an events management course together instead."
    lily"But I‚Äôve picked up things in this industry whenever we‚Äôve worked a function that was hosted at a hotel."
    lily"And it will be very handy here."
    show sc day2twdate1 t09
    lily"My sister and I are great at handling multiple event bookings at a time, and talking to folks from all walks of life."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"We just know how to find the right people to do the heavy lifting for us, if you know what I mean?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    mc"Yeah, so you just assign jobs to the people you know can get the job you need to be done."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"Precisely."
    mc"(Lily is more intelligent than I first realised.)"
    mc"(I should consider picking her brain some more if I want to be brought up to speed with the ins and outs of a hotel hosting major events.)"
    # (Ivy gets off her phone call)"
    show sc day2twdate1 t26
    ivy"Mind if I join you guys?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t24
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc day2twdate1 t24","sc day2twdate1 t24x","v_pt_image_index_32")
    mc"Oh, yes of course you can Ivy."
    # (Ivy sits down)"
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom

    show sc day2twdate1 t28
    ivy"Sorry about that. I had an important client on the phone. I never thought my conversation with him would ever end!"
    mc"Yeah, your sister told me a little bit about the kind of clients that you sometimes have to deal with."
    show sc day2twdate1 t27
    ivy"It‚Äôs all part of the job!"
    show sc day2twdate1 t18
    lily"But everything‚Äôs okay for this weekend sis?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t35
    ivy"Yeah it‚Äôs fine, all arrangements have been made and everything has been booked, finalised, and paid for."
    show sc day2twdate1 t21
    lily"Awesome!"
    # [Stay quiet / Ask for more details]"
    show sc day2twdate1 t34
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc day2twdate1 t34","sc day2twdate1 t34x","v_pt_image_index_33")
    mc"(Hmm...)"
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom

    menu:
        "Stay quiet":
            show sc day2twdate1 t32
            # (scene continues below)"
        "Ask for more details"(wt="Best choice"):
            show sc day2twdate1 t32
            mc"It sounds like it‚Äôs a pretty huge event that you two have on your hands."
            mc"Care to share any other details about it with me?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t31
            ivy"There isn‚Äôt honestly much to tell [y_name]. It‚Äôs just another event for us, another payday."
            show sc day2twdate1 t34
            ivy"And besides, we‚Äôve been asked by our client to keep the details of the party confidential."
            show sc day2twdate1 t35
            ivy"So even we can‚Äôt speak to anyone about this weekend's function."
            $ tw_points = change_stat(tw_points,1,"Lily and Ivy")
            show sc day2twdate1 t18
            lily"Yeah, that‚Äôs mentioned in the contract that we had drawn up I‚Äôm afraid."
            # (Lily and Ivy smile at each other)"
            show sc day2twdate1 t34
            mc"Oh, sure thing. I understand. Forget I even asked."
            mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ It still seems a little strange to me though, even if it‚Äôs just a private party going on in town.)"
            mc"(And I wonder what the reason was for the girls giving each other that look just now?)"
            mc"(It almost feels like there‚Äôs a hidden joke that I missed, or that they‚Äôre hiding something from me.)"
            mc"(Maybe it‚Äôs just me‚Ä¶)"

    show sc day2twdate1 t32
    mc"So, have you and Lily planned many other events in town?"
    ivy"Actually, Lily and I are only new to the Sunshine Bay area, as we moved down here from Seaside a few weeks ago."
    show sc day2twdate1 t36
    ivy"So we‚Äôre moving into uncharted territories..."
    show sc day2twdate1 t34
    ivy"But we saw so much potential here before deciding to make the move."
    show sc day2twdate1 t32
    mc"I see‚Ä¶ I guess that leads me to my next question."
    mc"How do you both know [s_name]?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t13
    lily"Through the hotel management course!"
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"I mean, just like me and Ivy, she didn‚Äôt go the distance with that course, but we stayed in touch, and she even came to a couple of parties we hosted up in Seaside."
    mc"Really?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t33
    ivy"Yeah, [s_name] sure knows how to have a good time. I tell you, she gets a bit wild and flirty when she‚Äôs had a few drinks in her."
    show sc day2twdate1 t34
    mc"Is that right? "
    show sc day2twdate1 t33
    ivy"Oh yeah."
    ivy"The three of us went to a house party when we were in our first year of college, and she was so drunk that she was dancing on top of a table about an hour after we arrived."
    show sc day2twdate1 t34
    ivy"That was quite a night for her, even though she didn‚Äôt remember much from it."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"So in a nutshell, more than anything, my sister and I just want to help you and [s_name] get the hotel back to where it should be, and that starts with bringing in some major business in for you both."
    lily"It won‚Äôt be easy, but Ivy and I aren‚Äôt afraid of a challenge."
    mc"Well that‚Äôs great to hear."
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    lily"Did you have any questions or concerns of your own? Is there anything else that you‚Äôd like to know about our events?"
    mc"I guess I‚Äôd like to know what it takes to be a highly skilled events coordinator like you and your sister."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"Oh, you mean aside from time, patience, and working incredibly hard for five or six days each week?"
    mc"Sure, but what are the main tasks that are involved with putting on a successful event?"
    show sc day2twdate1 t34
    ivy"There are five things that we make sure that we do every time we host an event."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"These things you would need to know, to memorise, and to learn them in a specific order."
    lily"Care to guess what the first thing is?"
    # (Lily leans forward, lifting one finger)"
    # ***The mini-game is related to the service or skill they want to bring to the hotel."
    # The MC will need to know how to run an event in order to gain a star."
    # - Three options per step. If the player gets one wrong, then they have to go back to the start again."
    # - Once they get the other three in the correct order, then they can proceed to the next scene in the game."
    # They will also gain a gold star for ‚ÄúEvents Quality‚Äù (more on this at another time)"
    # - The walkthrough will help players for this scene with the right combination."
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    mc"Uhh‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm not sure."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    lily"Okay, I‚Äôll make this easier by giving you the first two."
    lily"So what you need first off is to create an event budget and stick to it."
    lily"You would ask your client or business how much they would like to spend on the event."
    lily"That way, if you‚Äôre as experienced as me and Ivy are, then we know straight off the things we can and cannot afford."
    lily"We always try to not use all of their budget up, which our clients really appreciate."
    mc"Okay, that makes sense. And the second step?"
    lily"Right, so we already know which venue we‚Äôd have in mind, so after that, we would contact and manage things with our suppliers for the event."
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    lily"What do you think that includes?"
    mc"I don‚Äôt know, I suppose things like the lighting at the event, hiring caterers, audiovisual if it‚Äôs requested."
    show sc day2twdate1 t34
    ivy"Yes, perfect examples!"
    ivy"We also take into consideration health and safety, fire exits, the number of staff required for the event."
    show sc day2twdate1 t32
    ivy"After that, what do you think comes next [y_name]?"
    # *FIRST PART (*START HERE if the player failed to get the right combination)"
    # [Marketing and promotion / Design and Styling / Post-event analysis]"
    menu:
        "Marketing and promotion":
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Marketing and promotion?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t10
            lily"Yes, that‚Äôs a very important component of managing an event. What next? "
        "Design and Styling"(wt="Best choice"):
            $ v_twins_date1_choice1 = True
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Design and styling the event?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t10
            lily"Yeah, the client may request a certain theme or style for the event."
            lily"It could be a black and white themed party or a masquerade ball, so how the venue is decorated and set up needs to be a match."
            lily"What comes next?"
        "Post-event analysis":
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Post-event analysis?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t10
            lily"Yes, that‚Äôs a very important component of managing an event, but that comes at the very end [y_name]."
            show sc day2twdate1 t13
            lily"You jumped the trigger there, haha!"
            show sc day2twdate1 t10
            lily"What comes next?"
    # *SECOND PART"
    # [Managing risk / Post-event analysis / Marketing and promotion]"
    show sc day2twdate1 t32
    menu:
        "Managing risk":
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Managing risk?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t34
            ivy"Yes, that‚Äôs a part of it, but it usually comes after the Marketing and Promotion side of event management."
        "Post-event analysis":
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Post-event analysis?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t34
            ivy"Yes, that‚Äôs a very important component of managing an event, but that comes at the very end [y_name]."
            show sc day2twdate1 t33
            ivy"You jumped the trigger there, haha!"
        "Marketing and promotion"(wt="Best choice"):
            $ v_twins_date1_choice2 = True
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Marketing and promotion?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t34
            ivy"Yes, that‚Äôs a very important component of managing an event."
            show sc day2twdate1 t10
            lily"And it‚Äôs something that I do a lot of once we have all the previous information available to us."
            lily"We hit everywhere we can to promote an event, especially if it‚Äôs an open-invite for it."
            show sc day2twdate1 t34
            ivy"So online, in the paper, signboards in bus shelters, park benches and so forth."
            ivy"Otherwise, if it‚Äôs an invite-only event, then I‚Äôll find the most appropriate invitations for the event in question."
            show sc day2twdate1 t10
            lily"We have plenty of examples on file for clients to choose from."
            mc"That‚Äôs certainly handy!"
            show sc day2twdate1 t13
            lily"As I said before, we‚Äôre very well-organised."
            # (scene continues)"
    show sc day2twdate1 t34
    ivy"You‚Äôre going to have to review and manage risk at some point, as well as setting a daily schedule to get everything done in time for the event."
    mc"Sure, that makes sense."
    show sc day2twdate1 t11
    lily"All right, so it‚Äôs the end of the event‚Ä¶"
    lily"What do you think we would do once the party or major event has finally concluded?"
    # *THIRD PART"
    # [Tidy up / Post-event analysis / Event success]"
    menu:
        "Tidy up":
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Tidy up?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t31
            ivy"Well, you have your allocated staff to do that for you [y_name]."
            ivy"Us event coordinators will do anything, NOT to get our hands dirty, remember?"
            mc"Right, of course."
        "Post-event analysis"(wt="Best choice"):
            $ v_twins_date1_choice3 = True
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Post-event analysis?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t10
            lily"Yes, that‚Äôs a very important component of managing an event, and that comes at the very end [y_name]."
            lily"This may include writing up a short summary of the event..."
            lily"And it would have a section for both parties, us and the client, to sign if we‚Äôre both happy with how everything went."
        "Event success":
            mc"Uh‚Ä¶ Maybe promoting your successful event to the guests, or on your site?"
            show sc day2twdate1 t32
            ivy"Well, the guests at the event will know by the end of the event whether they want our services or not."
            ivy"So there‚Äôd be no point in trying to promote it to them at the end."
            ivy"And anything we write up about specific functions on our site usually doesn‚Äôt happen until a week or two after it‚Äôs concluded."
    # ‚ÄúIf the player chose a wrong step, this scene will happen next‚Äù"



    if v_twins_date1_choice1 == False or v_twins_date1_choice2 == False or v_twins_date1_choice3 == False:

        show sc day2twdate1 t11
        mc"So, how did I do?"
        show sc day2twdate1 t12
        lily"Well, you were kind of on the right track, but your answers weren't quite right."
        mc"Damn..."
        show sc day2twdate1 t34
        ivy"That's okay. At least you tried."
    else:
        # ‚ÄúIf the player chose the right combination, this scene will happen next‚Äù"
        $ tw_points = change_stat(tw_points,3,"Lily and Ivy")
        show sc day2twdate1 t13
        lily"Well done, I think you may just have it in you to be an events planner in the near future!"
        # (One ‚ÄúHotel Events STAR gained‚Äù - In the menu - A star is added next to the Twins - Hotel Events column)"
        show sc day2twdate1 t10
        mc"Haha, I don‚Äôt know about that. But thanks for the crash course Lily."
        lily"It was my pleasure."
    show sc day2twdate1 t20
    lily"Look, Ivy and I have to be at this client‚Äôs place very shortly, so we‚Äôre just about to lock up for lunch."
    show sc day2twdate1 t10
    jump lb_day2_twins_date1_1

label lb_day2_twins_date1_1:
    lily"Do you think we could come by to the hotel to meet you and [s_name] sometime tomorrow?"

label lb_day2_twins_date1_2:
    mc"Oh, sure, that would be great! I‚Äôll let her know and I‚Äôll get her to call you to work out a time."
    show sc day2twdate1 t33
    ivy"Excellent!"
    show sc day2twdate1 t34
    mc"Great! Okay, I best be on my way then."
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc day2twdate1 t39
    with dissolve
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc day2twdate1 t39","sc day2twdate1 t39x","v_pt_image_index_34")
    mc"Thank you for your time ladies."
    # (He extends his right hand for her to give him a handshake)"
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom

    lily"Our pleasure."
    # (they shake hands)"
    show sc day2twdate1 t41
    ivy"And [y_name], can you give this to [s_name] for us when you see her?"
    # (Lily kisses him on the cheek)"
    $ renpy.sound.play("sound effects/01/02/double_kiss_sound_effect.mp3", loop=False, fadeout=1.0, fadein=1.0)
    show sc day2twdate1 t43
    mc"(Oh!)"
    show sc day2twdate1 t44
    mc"(Woah!! I certainly wasn‚Äôt expecting a kiss from one or even both of them!)"
    stop sound
    show sc day2twdate1 t40
    lily"[s_name] will know what it means [y_name]."
    show sc day2twdate1 t39
    mc"Uh, sure thing ladies. I guess I‚Äôll be seeing you both soon."
    lily"Bye [y_name]‚Ä¶"
    ivy"You sure will!"
    # (MC walks out of the office)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc day2oceanlook l11
    with dissolve
    mc"(Well, I learned quite a lot from Ivy and Lily in that short meeting.)"
    mc"(They‚Äôve given me some insight into the world of events management, but I still have plenty of things I can learn from them both.)"
    show sc day2oceanlook l14
    mc"(And I wonder what those kisses on the cheek for [s_name] meant?)"
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ They‚Äôre a funny pair of sisters, thats for sure‚Ä¶)"
    if v_char_ashley_cancall == False and v_char_victoria_cancall == False and v_char_c_cancall == False:
        show sc day2oceanlook l12
        mc"(Okay, it‚Äôs time that I face the music and talk to [s_name].)"
        show sc day2oceanlook l13
        mc"(I still have my trust issues with her, but for the sake of the hotel and the fact that I still have a job to do here, we need to come to a peaceful resolution that works for both of us.)"
        mc"(Even if it means that [s_name] and I still need to keep a distance from each other after the workday has ended‚Ä¶)"
        scene black
        with dissolve
        scene black
        with Pause (2)
        jump lb_day2_nicole_calls

    else:
        scene black
