label lb_day2_ashleydate1_1:
    ash"Once I was pregnant with [s_name], I was pretty much disowned by my parents."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a22
    ash"They had a very strict, religious upbringing you see, and they saw it as a sin for me to have a child before getting married."

label lb_day2_ashleydate1_2:
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    ash"Their attitude towards me has always been rather strange, because something similar happened to my sister Trisha."
    ash"[c_name] doesn‚Äôt know who her real father is, yet my parents never came down hard on Trisha for that."
    ash"I was always the black sheep in our family though, and she was always their favourite."
    ash"So by the time I gave birth to [s_name], I decided to completely cut ties with my parents."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"I never contacted them and they never got in touch with me."
    ash"I didn‚Äôt have anything to do with them until Trisha called me to say that they‚Äôd both unfortunately passed away in tragic circumstances a few years ago."
    mc"Oh, I‚Äôm so sorry."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a24
    ash"No it‚Äôs okay. Anyways, in their will, they left the rights to the hotel in my name, and in Trisha's as well."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"Not wanting anything to do with the hotel, I made a decision that I was going to eventually leave it to my daughter."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    mc"You seem to know a bit about property Ashley."
    mc"Why would you give it up so easily, when it‚Äôs in such a prime location with so much potential?"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"Because it has little value nowadays [y_name]."
    ash"[s_name] doesn‚Äôt know that it‚Äôs still depreciating in value due to the market and the slow business that it‚Äôs experienced in recent months."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    ash"I guess I hoped that someone would put in an offer to [s_name] and [c_name] to buy it from them..."
    ash"But most investors who have done their homework know that taking over the rights to the hotel is a poisoned chalice."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"I think the lightning that struck the lighthouse a while back is a sure sign of that."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    mc"Hmm‚Ä¶ Maybe. What about the past history of the hotel?"
    mc"Did your parents or Trisha ever find anything about it that could be useful?"
    # (Ashley uncrosses her legs)"
    ash"Well‚Ä¶ As [s_name] has probably made you aware by now, the hotel caters to females only, and that was always the places‚Äô biggest strength."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a23
    ash"Girls loved the camaraderie, and guys wished they could stay there, just so they could see what they were missing out on."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a20
    ash"And then there were the huge parties, the major events and so forth."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    mc"What kind of events are we talking about?"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a23
    ash"The hotel I was told used to host modelling events, fashion shows in the main hall, volleyball competitions on the beach for guests."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a17
    mc"Volleyball competitions?"
    ash"Yeah. The girls staying at the hotel would run a little tournament on weekends, if the weather was right."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a20
    ash"Guys would sit up on the hill to ogle them while they played as they‚Äôd be in their bikinis."
    ash"That was the closest that men would ever get to being allowed into the hotel area or the lighthouse."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"But those days are long gone. These kinds of events dried up a long time ago [y_name]."
    ash"You‚Äôd need a great event coordinator to be able to organise such a party, and for it to be run successfully. I just don‚Äôt see it happening."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a29
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ I wonder what the twins would think about these ideas, or attempting to revive the past?)"
    # (Ashley stretches herself out on the couch, like this - https://pixhost.to/show/232/133431405_screen-shot-2020-01-17-at-11-17-52-am.png - https://pixhost.to/show/232/133431407_screen-shot-2020-01-17-at-11-18-12-am.png)"

    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    mc"What about the lighthouse?"
    mc"As far as I‚Äôve been told, the globe will cost quite a sum of money to have replaced."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"It will, but even though the lighthouse has its issues, it‚Äôs another big reason why investors have been put off from buying the rights to the hotel."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    mc"It is? How come?"
    ash"Anyone who knows anything about property in Sunshine Bay is aware that if they buy the hotel, then the lighthouse has to remain the way it is."
    ash"A former mayor of the town was looking to sponsor an initiative to have the lighthouse knocked down to pave the way to use the land that it currently stands on."
    ash"However, the Sunshine Bay Preservation Society wanted to keep the lighthouse preserved the way it is, as it‚Äôs a huge part of the town‚Äôs history and heritage."
    ash"And the vast majority of people who live in the bay area made sure the mayor heard their voices, which is why it still remains today."
    mc"So what you‚Äôre saying is, if someone invests in the hotel, or wants to buy it from [s_name] and [c_name], then the lighthouse cannot be changed in any way?"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a17
    ash"Precisely! It‚Äôs protected by Sunshine Bay local law."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    ash"I mean, it would take someone with incredible pulling power and the finances for that law to change."
    ash"But so far, no one has shown any real interest, even though the land itself could be worth plenty of money if they were to get rid of the lighthouse."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a17
    ash"So for now, [s_name] has nothing to worry about. I‚Äôm not sure for how much longer though."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a29
    mc"Yeah, I know what you mean."
    mc"(So the lighthouse is putting potential investors off. That‚Äôs a little comforting to know.)"
    show screen scr_rewards("sc day2ashdate1 a25b","v_rewards_ashley_13")
    show sc day2ashdate1 a27
    ash"Anyways, enough about the hotel. What about you?"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a28
    ash"You‚Äôve got a girlfriend back home. Are you going to marry this‚Ä¶ Nicole is it?"
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc day2ashdate1 a29
    mc"Yeah that‚Äôs her."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a26
    mc"Marriage hasn‚Äôt really come up in discussion to be honest."
    mc"Our jobs and paying our mortgage off has been our main priority."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a25
    ash"Well sure, having a girlfriend, a great job and a nice place to live are all well and good, but life is short, you know?"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a28
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc day2ashdate1 a28","sc day2ashdate1 a28x","v_pt_image_index_27")
    ash"In my experiences, I‚Äôve always tried to entertain new ideas, new challenges, new people."
    ash"I‚Äôve been with a few different men since your father, and there‚Äôs no harm in trying other people on, if you know what I mean?"
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom

    show sc day2ashdate1 a26
    mc"Yeah, I don‚Äôt know about that Ashley. I‚Äôm pretty devoted to my partner, as I know Nicole is to me. I wouldn‚Äôt even consider cheating on her."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a25
    ash"Look, I‚Äôm sure that she loves you. And I wasn‚Äôt talking about cheating. "
    show sc day2ashdate1 a28
    ash"You‚Äôre still young [y_name]. I mean, does anyone truly know what they want when they're in the early to mid-twenties? I certainly didn‚Äôt."
    mc"And you do now?"
    ash"I know for sure that I like to keep my options open, that I like to experiment, and I like to have fun."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a27
    ash"Is that a good enough answer?"

    menu:
        "It sure is"(wt="Best choice"):
            #‚Äù +1 ASHLEY POINT"
            $ ash_points = change_stat(ash_points,1,"Ashley")
            show sc day2ashdate1 a26
            mc"It sure is!"
            #(Ashley shows an intrigued face)"
            show sc day2ashdate1 a34
            ash"(That sounded like he was certainly interested. Hmm‚Ä¶)"
        "I‚Äôm not sure":
            show sc day2ashdate1 a26
            mc"Uh, to be honest, I‚Äôm not really sure."
            show sc day2ashdate1 a27
            ash"Haha, that‚Äôs fair enough."
        "I guess so":
            mc"Uhh, I guess so."
            #(Ashley shows a plain straight face)"
            show sc day2ashdate1 a35
            ash"(That didn‚Äôt sound like he was at all interested. Hmm‚Ä¶)"



    show sc day2ashdate1 a28
    ash"All I‚Äôm saying is to keep an open mind, meet new people, explore, just like I have. And not just with my current job."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a26
    ash"You‚Äôre here in Sunshine Bay for three months, which is a long time to be away from someone you love and care about like I‚Äôm sure you do with Nicole."
    ash"But she‚Äôs also away from you for three months."
    ash"How do you know that she‚Äôs not going to try and have some fun of her own while you‚Äôre away from her?"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a29
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Surely she wouldn‚Äôt. Then again, what if she does?)"
    mc"(Nicole did say to me before I left that we‚Äôd both know what we‚Äôd truly want after these three months apart are over.)"
    mc"(Could she have meant us not being together anymore?)"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"I know you don‚Äôt want to hear this [y_name], but your father came around at a time in my life that I needed someone to save me."
    ash"I did genuinely love him for that and many other things, and I still appreciate everything he did for me and [s_name]."
    ash"But I just wasn‚Äôt in love with him anymore, and he just couldn‚Äôt accept that. So I had to leave."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    mc"I have no idea what happened between you two, because I was only fifteen at the time..."
    mc"But what on earth could‚Äôve possibly caused you and my Dad to hate each other so much, that you decided to move back here to Sunshine Bay?"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a24
    ash"(Sigh‚Ä¶)"
    ash"I can‚Äôt talk about it with you [y_name]. It‚Äôs just hard for me to discuss right now, and with you of all people."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    mc"(What the hell does that mean?)"
    mc"I don‚Äôt understand Ashley. You and Dad seemed great together."
    mc"And then all of a sudden, it felt like you were always arguing. It was like a switch had been flicked. "
    mc"Wait! My Dad wasn‚Äôt violent with you, was he?"
    mc"(Is that why she‚Äôs finding it so hard to discuss the past with me?)"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a24
    ash"No, no! He never hit me or anything like that. Your Dad deep down is a good man."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    ash"I mean, he had a temper, but I could handle that."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"Look, [y_name], I think you were right when you said that it‚Äôs best that we don‚Äôt discuss your Dad."
    ash"So, if you don‚Äôt mind?"
    mc"Uh, okay. We won‚Äôt then."
    mc"(It‚Äôs true, I did say that to her. But that was out of anger after I‚Äôd had that call with my father.)"
    mc"(What is Ashley hiding from me? What did my Dad do to cause her and [s_name] to leave like that?)"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a17
    jump lb_day2_ashleydate1_3

label lb_day2_ashleydate1_3:
    ash"Look, [s_name] is a tough young woman. She‚Äôll figure this out."

label lb_day2_ashleydate1_4:
    ash"Plus with you by her side, I have even more faith that the two of you can turn the place around."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a20
    ash"You‚Äôre a smart young man [y_name], I can tell."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a17
    ash"You were when you were young and it was obvious that you were going to make something of yourself."
    ash"And that very ‚Äúsomething‚Äù could be right here in Sunshine Bay. If you want it to be that is."
    ash"You and [s_name] have the best qualities of me and your father. That much I can tell."
    ash"The two of you just need to find a median, to get yourselves on the same wavelength and not let the little issues turn into full-blown arguments."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a18
    mc"Yeah, that‚Äôs easier said than done Ashley. I just don't understand her or the way she thinks."
    ash"And you‚Äôre not expected to either. It‚Äôs just how we women are. Our minds think differently to yours. "
    show sc day2ashdate1 a19
    ash"You know, sorry to bring it up again, but I really do regret the way things ended between me and your father."
    ash"Maybe I overreacted at the time, rather than thinking things through and trying to work on our relationship."
    ash"But the thing you have to understand with me is that when I have my heart set on something, I rarely change my mind."
    show sc day2ashdate1 a22
    mc"So what‚Äôs the lesson here for me?"
    show sc day2ashdate1 a17
