label lb_opening_7:
    # (Gerald waits outside the burlesque house for Ashley to finish work)"
    scene sc opening95
    with dissolve
    lt"(Looks like she should be coming out, any minute now.)"
    show sc opening101
    lt"(I can‚Äôt let this rest. I know something happened between us last night.)"
    lt"(I have to know for sure what that ‚Äúsomething‚Äù was‚Ä¶)"
    # (Ashley walks out from the club, sees F)"
    show sc opening96
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc opening96","sc opening96x","v_pt_image_index_03")
    ash"Bye guys!"
    "Bye Ashley."
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom
    show sc opening102
    lt"Uhm... Hi..."
    show sc opening103
    ash"Hi..."
    show sc opening98
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc opening98","sc opening98x","v_pt_image_index_04")

    ash"You just don‚Äôt give up, do you?"
    lt"Well, it‚Äôs not like I‚Äôve never been thrown out of a club before. And I can handle myself just fine."
    ash"I can see that."
    ash"So, what is that you would like from me officer?"
    lt"Just to talk. Say like, five minutes of your time."
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom
    show sc opening102
    lt"After that, if you don‚Äôt like what you hear, then I‚Äôll never bother you again. How does that sound? "
    show sc opening98
    ash"Hmm, you‚Äôre putting a lot on the line there."
    show sc opening99
    ash"But how do I know that I can trust you? Or how do you know that I‚Äôm not some nut-job, psycho killer?"
    show sc opening100
    lt"Well I can‚Äôt answer either of those questions to be honest. But I‚Äôm certainly willing to find out!"
    show sc opening98
    ash"Haha, I do love a risk-taker I‚Äôll admit."
    show sc opening100
    lt"I also believe that sometimes in life, you just have to take a chance on people, you know?"
    lt"I‚Äôve made the first move, now I‚Äôm just waiting to see how you respond, ma‚Äôam."
    show sc opening98
    ash"Okay, well first of all, please don‚Äôt call me ma‚Äôam. Ashley is fine."
    show sc opening103
    ash"Um look, I‚Äôm sorry if I embarrassed you back stage before Gerald. "
    ash"It‚Äôs just that the club owners don‚Äôt really like it if we converse with the patrons, especially if they‚Äôre not buying a drink."
    ash"Nor would they like it if they saw me with you out the front here."
    show sc opening98
    ash"So would you like to walk me home?"
    ash"It‚Äôs only a few blocks from here, and that way we can talk on the way there."
    lt"Oh yeah, that would be great!"
    # (Gerald and Ashley leave and start walking away from the club)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc opening104
    with dissolve
    ash"So uhh‚Ä¶ You‚Äôre a naval officer I'm guessing?"
    show sc opening110
    lt"Yeah, for a few years now."
    lt"Our ship had some technical issues so Sunshine Bay was the closest place for us to port."
    show sc opening111
    ash"And how long do you think you‚Äôll be in town for?"
    lt"I‚Äôm not too sure. A couple more days I suspect."
    lt"How about you? Have you been working at the club for long?"
    show sc opening107
    ash"About eight years now. It‚Äôs not the greatest job in the world, but I‚Äôm good at it."
    ash"And it keeps a roof over our heads."
    show sc opening111
    lt"Oh‚Ä¶ You‚Äôre married then I take it?"
    show sc opening107
    ash"Haha, no, not married."
    show sc opening112
    lt"(Hmm, she has a boyfriend, I knew it‚Ä¶)"
    show sc opening111
    lt"Really? I must say I‚Äôm very surprised."
    show sc opening108
    ash"Well, I have my reasons. What about yourself? Married? Kids?"
    show sc opening110
    lt"Yeah um, I have a son actually. He just turned eleven."
    show sc opening107
    ash"You and your wife must be pretty happy I imagine."
    show sc opening111
    ash"But what would she think if you were escorting the likes of me back to her home at this time of night?"
    show sc opening112
    lt"Yeah uhh‚Ä¶ She um, she passed away early last year, from breast cancer."
    show sc opening108
    ash"Oh‚Ä¶ I am so sorry. That was very rude of me to presume."
    show sc opening111
    lt"It‚Äôs okay, you couldn‚Äôt have known. It hasn‚Äôt been easy on either of us, more so for my son."
    show sc opening111
    ash"So if you‚Äôre here, who looks after him?"
    lt"He has a nanny fortunately. I‚Äôm usually home at least once a month, so I‚Äôve still been able to see him grow up at least."
    show sc opening107
    ash"That‚Äôs good. You sound like you‚Äôre a great father if you‚Äôre still able to return home pretty often, despite the job that you have."
    show sc opening105
    lt"Thanks, I try to be. And you get special privileges as a Lieutenant."
    lt"I'd love to be able to see him more and to find a nice place somewhere to settle down."
    show sc opening110
    lt"And to find a job that would keep me closer to home more often."
    show sc opening107
    ash"Yeah, I know what you mean."
    show sc opening111
    ash"Um, my place is just around the corner from here, and there‚Äôs something I‚Äôd like you to see."
    show sc opening107
    ash"Maybe you‚Äôd like to come in for a nightcap?"
    show sc opening105
    lt"Oh, okay. That would be nice."
    lt"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Well this is going well.)"
    lt"(She hasn‚Äôt blown me off, and she seems really easy-going and great at making conversation.)"
    show sc opening111
    lt"(Hmm‚Ä¶ I wonder what she wants to show me?)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # END SCENE"
    # NEXT SCENE: Opening Part 1 - Scene 8 - Sunshine Bay - Day 2 - House Interior"






