    show sc opening129
    ash"I‚Äôd rather [s_name] have no father at all, than someone who doesn‚Äôt want to be her Dad. Even despite our circumstances‚Ä¶"
    show sc opening132
    lt"Look, Ashley, I know we don‚Äôt know much about each other, but I really do feel you were right about what you said back at the club, before I was thrown out."
    show sc opening136
    ash"About what exactly?"
    lt"About us having a meaningful connection."
    show sc opening139
    lt"This is going to sound crazy, but I really did feel something last night, and I know deep down you did too."
    show sc opening146
    ash"Please Gerald, I don‚Äôt want you to feel guilty about any of this, or our situation."
    show sc opening145
    ash"We‚Äôre doing just fine, and once I get my psychology degree, me and [s_name] will be all set."
    show sc opening140
    lt"(Hmm... There are so many things I wanna say to her right now.)"
    show sc opening139
    lt"Ashley, let me help you and [s_name]."
    # (Gerald puts his hands upon Ashley‚Äôs)"
